text: Bruna Vuletić (born 3 July 1999) is a Croatian taekwondo practitioner. She won a bronze medal in lightweight at the 2019 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Caroline Santos in the semifinal. In 2019, she represented Croatia at the 2019 Summer Universiade in Naples, Italy and she won one of the bronze medals in the women's 62 kg event. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Croatian female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Medalists at the 2019 Summer Universiade Category:Universiade medalists in taekwondo Category:Universiade bronze medalists for Croatia
